gui.model.domain

Class DomainModel

  • java.lang.Object
    • gui.model.domain.DomainModel

  • public class DomainModel
extends java.lang.Object
    DomainModel class represents a domain model of a GUI. A domain model can be extracted from a Window, Dialog or any other Scene. Each domain model has a name which is usually extracted from the scene name. This name represents the name of the domain, which is described by the domain model.
    Domain model is a tree structure, which contains terms (Term class). The root of this structure is the root term. Each term contains domain information and a list of child terms. The root term usually contains the domain information extracted from the scene component.
    Domain model also contains a reference to the scene, from which it was extracted.
    Domain models are extracted using the DEAL method, which is implemented in DomainModelGenerator class.
    Author:
    Michaela Bacikova, Slovakia, michaela.bacikova@tuke.sk

      • shiftSingleChildLeafs

        public boolean shiftSingleChildLeafs()
        If there are terms, which have only one child and the child is a leaf, then this leaf is moved to its grandparent and its parent is removed.
        Parent-Grandparent-Leaf ==> Parent-Leaf
        Returns:
        true if anything was shifted, false otherwise
